<p/>
<b>Notes:</b>In Chinese, when people want to express something that has happened ,they use 了 le, no tone at the end of a verb. For example: 花了我不少钱—cost me a lot of money. Also Chinese use a lot of interjections when they talk. The most common ones are: 啊 and 呢.
