      <dc:date>2009-04-24T23:00:00Z</dc:date>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://content.visualmandarin.com/exercises/images/small_1034504901.jpg"/></p>
<p>The sentence order in Chinese is quite the same as in English, but Chinese verbs are very regular in form. This means that they do not change according to person, number or tense.<p/>
In this lesson, Alice (as a teacher) meets her new student  - Zhaomin. Zhaomin never been to school before and doesn't have a clue what it is all about. Also his parents did not really bother telling him much about it. Otherwise he would have not brought this strange item to his first day in school. Are you curious? If you want to know please tune in to this lesson!
<p/>
What you will learn in this lesson:<br/>
- Action verbs<br/>
- Indirect object<br/>
- Question word<br/>
- Naming<br/>
